From the wiki

Johnny Staccato is an American private detective series starring John Cassavetes which ran for 27 episodes on NBC from September 10, 1959 through March 24, 1960.

1-1 	"The Naked Truth" 	September 10, 1959 	Staccato investigates a scandal magazine's blackmail scheme that could end the promising career of a young male vocalist.
